         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Borough of Warrnambool ¶ Town Hall ¶ Dec 11 1878 ¶ Sir ¶  ¶ I am requested by the Borough Council of Warrnambool to ask you if you let us know the best month in the year for sowing and transplanting o...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">78.12.11</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Charles Cramer</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Letter press copy book 5, p. 73, Borough Council records, Warrnambool, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">Transcribed 7.10.78. To be proofed.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">For a summary of this letter see: Minute book 8, p. 449.</p>
               </note>Borough of Warrnambool</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Town Hall</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Dec 11 1878</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am requested by the Borough Council of Warrnambool to ask you if you let us know the best month in the year for sowing and transplanting on the sand at coast and whether the sowing of seeds over a large surface or adopting transplanting would be most effective, or if both courses might be most advantageously pursued.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Council planted a lot of various seeds this season but think they must have been planted late, as they have not succeeded well<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The<seg style="font-style: italic; "> Warrnambool standard </seg>added that: 'Cr. Harris remarked that the seed sowing had been a failure. In the first place, it had not been sown at the proper time, and after being sown the seed was destroyed by the first storm. He thought transplanting was the only effectual remedy. Cr. Watson was sure that nothing but couch grass could survive the action of the drifting sand.' (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Warrnambool standard</seg>, 12 December 1878, p. 2).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I am</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your obedient Sert</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>C. A. Cramer</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Town Clerk</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron Von Muëller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Govt Botanist<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See also M to C. Cramer, December 1878.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
